### Configure Text Field Type in Payload (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/text.mdx

To integrate a Text Field into your Payload CMS configuration, define its type as 'text' within your Field Config. This setup ensures a string is saved to the database and a text input is available in the Admin Panel.

```typescript
import type { Field } from 'payload'

export const MyTextField: Field = {
  // ...
  type: 'text' // highlight-line
}
```

--------------------------------

### Define a Text Field in Payload Collection Config

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/overview.mdx

This example shows how to define a simple 'text' field within a Payload Collection configuration. The `fields` array contains an object for each field, specifying its `name` and `type` properties. This field will store a string value in the database and be rendered as a text input in the Admin Panel.

```ts
import type { CollectionConfig } from 'payload'

export const Page: CollectionConfig = {
  slug: 'pages',
  // highlight-start
  fields: [
    {
      name: 'field',
      type: 'text',
    },
  ],
  // highlight-end
}
```

--------------------------------

### Create a Custom Text Field Server Component in PayloadCMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/text.mdx

This code defines a custom server-side React component for a PayloadCMS Text Field. It utilizes `TextFieldServerComponent` from 'payload' and renders the base `@payloadcms/ui` TextField, passing along necessary props such as `clientField`, `path`, `schemaPath`, and `permissions`.

```tsx
import type React from 'react'
import { TextField } from '@payloadcms/ui'
import type { TextFieldServerComponent } from 'payload'

export const CustomTextFieldServer: TextFieldServerComponent = ({
  clientField,
  path,
  schemaPath,
  permissions,
}) => {
  return (
    <TextField
      field={clientField}
      path={path}
      schemaPath={schemaPath}
      permissions={permissions}
    />
  )
}
```

--------------------------------

### Define a Required Text Field in PayloadCMS Collection Configuration

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/text.mdx

This example illustrates the basic structure for defining a required Text Field within a PayloadCMS `CollectionConfig`. It specifies the field's `name`, sets its `type` to 'text', and ensures it's mandatory by setting `required` to `true`.

```ts
import type { CollectionConfig } from 'payload'

export const ExampleCollection: CollectionConfig = {
  slug: 'example-collection',
  fields: [
    {
      name: 'pageTitle', // required
      type: 'text', // required
      required: true,
    },
  ],
}
```

--------------------------------

### Create a Custom Text Field Client Component in PayloadCMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/text.mdx

This snippet shows how to implement a custom client-side React component for a PayloadCMS Text Field. Marked with `'use client'`, it leverages `TextFieldClientComponent` and efficiently passes all incoming props directly to the base `@payloadcms/ui` TextField for rendering, allowing for client-specific behavior or styling.

```tsx
'use client'
import React from 'react'
import { TextField } from '@payloadcms/ui'
import type { TextFieldClientComponent } from 'payload'

export const CustomTextFieldClient: TextFieldClientComponent = (props) => {
  return <TextField {...props} />
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Text Field in Payload CMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/FIELDS.md

Define a basic text field with validation, localization, and admin UI customization. Supports constraints like minLength, maxLength, uniqueness, and conditional visibility in the admin interface.

```typescript
import type { TextField } from 'payload'

const textField: TextField = {
  name: 'title',
  type: 'text',
  required: true,
  unique: true,
  minLength: 5,
  maxLength: 100,
  index: true,
  localized: true,
  defaultValue: 'Default Title',
  validate: (value) => Boolean(value) || 'Required',
  admin: {
    placeholder: 'Enter title...',
    position: 'sidebar',
    condition: (data) => data.showTitle === true,
  },
}
```

