### Define Custom Server Component Field Label in Payload CMS (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/text.mdx

This TypeScript code defines a custom server component for a Payload CMS field label. It utilizes `@payloadcms/ui`'s `FieldLabel` component and receives `clientField`, `path`, and `required` props, rendering a label based on the field's properties.

```tsx
import React from 'react'
import { FieldLabel } from '@payloadcms/ui'
import type { TextFieldLabelServerComponent } from 'payload'

export const CustomTextFieldLabelServer: TextFieldLabelServerComponent = ({
  clientField,
  path,
  required,
}) => {
  return (
    <FieldLabel
      label={clientField?.label || clientField?.name}
      path={path}
      required={clientField?.required}
    />
  )
}
```

